cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence-to-sequence models and natural language processing tasks such as abstractive document summarization and machine translation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses neural attention mechanisms and their adaptation via amortized variational inference. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with deep learning models and their optimization. The paper also mentions video captioning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of context vectors and their inference could also place this paper under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
